            "title": "Polar decompositions and procrustes problems in finite dimensional indefinite scalar product spaces",
            "abstract": "The problem of determining for given matrices X, Y in Rn\u00d7N an orthogonal matrix U in Rn\u00d7n such that the Frobenium norm of the residual matrix UX-Y becomes a minimum is called the orthogonal Procrustes problem. It is a well-known fact that the wanted matrix can be obtained via a polar decomposition YXT = UM in which it appears as the isometric factor. In the presented thesis generalisations of this problem in non-Euclidean real or complex vector spaces are considered in which the underlying geometry is based on an indefinite scalar product. Such a scalar product can always be written in the form (H.,.) where H is a nonsingular selfadjoint matrix having positive and negative eigenvalues, and (.,.) denotes the canonical scalar product. In preparation of these investigations several subspace decompositions and statements on H-orthogonal bases are derived ...",
